WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:41.208 --> 00:00:42.208
[bombs whistling]

3
00:00:53.262 --> 00:00:55.181
[groaning]

4
00:01:02.104 --> 00:01:05.524
[distant battle]

5
00:01:25.002 --> 00:01:26.642
All the souls who
have faithfully departed

6
00:01:26.670 --> 00:01:28.297
through the mercy of God

7
00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:29.465
rest in peace.

8
00:01:51.362 --> 00:01:52.488
[grunts]

9
00:01:53.906 --> 00:01:56.075
MAN:
For the king!

10
00:01:56.158 --> 00:01:57.158
[men shouting]

11
00:02:07.253 --> 00:02:09.255
Mademoiselle. are you hurt?

12
00:02:09.338 --> 00:02:11.924
No. but we will never
defeat the English

13
00:02:12.007 --> 00:02:14.718
if we do not get these
soldiers across the river.

14
00:02:26.397 --> 00:02:28.440
Pour la France!

15
00:02:28.524 --> 00:02:32.611
- Pour la France!
- Pour la France!

16
00:02:32.695 --> 00:02:34.738
Pour la France!

17
00:02:34.822 --> 00:02:36.532
[shouting]

18
00:02:38.409 --> 00:02:40.744
Vive la France!

19
00:02:43.539 --> 00:02:46.208
Vive la France!

20
00:02:47.877 --> 00:02:48.877
What's that commotion?

21
00:02:50.546 --> 00:02:52.590
Vive la France!

22
00:02:55.009 --> 00:02:58.095
Sir. they seem to
be waving a banner.

23
00:02:58.345 --> 00:02:59.345
Surrendering?

24
00:03:00.306 --> 00:03:01.348
No. sir.

25
00:03:01.432 --> 00:03:03.767
The solders seem to be roused.

26
00:03:03.851 --> 00:03:08.564
Vive la France!
Vive la France!

27
00:03:11.275 --> 00:03:14.361
You bring that flag bearer down.

28
00:03:14.445 --> 00:03:15.445
Aye. sir.

29
00:03:17.072 --> 00:03:19.241
Vive la France!

30
00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:23.329
Vive la France!

31
00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:27.875
[grunts]

32
00:03:30.252 --> 00:03:31.253
Ah!

33
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:46.060
Jean!

34
00:03:57.905 --> 00:04:00.115
<i>Joan of Arc
successfully displaced</i>

35
00:04:00.199 --> 00:04:02.534
with minimal disruption.

36
00:04:02.618 --> 00:04:06.038
<i>Auditory link and
vocal relay established.</i>

37
00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:09.041
<i>All dialects normalized.</i>

38
00:04:09.124 --> 00:04:11.585
<i>Joan. exit behind you.</i>

39
00:04:17.132 --> 00:04:18.926
<i>Follow the illuminated passage</i>

40
00:04:19.009 --> 00:04:21.929
<i>toward the red light for
integration and armament.</i>

41
00:04:22.012 --> 00:04:23.764
<i>Welcome to Crimson Havoc.</i>

42
00:04:56.672 --> 00:04:57.589
Welcome.

43
00:04:57.673 --> 00:04:59.883
My name is Aria Wellman.

44
00:04:59.967 --> 00:05:03.345
You all are among the deadliest
and most influential

45
00:05:03.429 --> 00:05:05.931
warriors the world
has ever known.

46
00:05:06.015 --> 00:05:06.932
Are we...

47
00:05:07.016 --> 00:05:08.559
[feedback]

48
00:05:08.642 --> 00:05:11.228
Speaking is going to take a
little bit of getting used to.

49
00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.939
As none of you can
speak modern English.

50
00:05:14.023 --> 00:05:16.316
a language interface was
applied during your transfer

51
00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:17.901
so that we can all communicate.

52
00:05:19.278 --> 00:05:22.489
Are we... deceased?

53
00:05:24.033 --> 00:05:25.367
Are you God?

54
00:05:26.618 --> 00:05:29.329
You are in the future.

55
00:05:29.413 --> 00:05:31.331
You have all traveled
through time.

56
00:05:31.415 --> 00:05:34.376
We are not dead?

57
00:05:34.460 --> 00:05:36.253
Mm-mm.

58
00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:38.756
We remain flesh and blood?

59
00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:42.051
- Yes.
- Then I can kill you.

60
00:05:42.134 --> 00:05:43.552
You can be killed.

61
00:05:43.635 --> 00:05:45.429
All of you.

62
00:05:45.512 --> 00:05:47.347
That's kind of the point.

63
00:05:47.431 --> 00:05:51.977
You are here to fight
in our tournament.

64
00:05:52.061 --> 00:05:56.106
I represent a company called
the Temporal Combat Authority.

65
00:05:56.190 --> 00:05:59.818
Our company has discovered
a way to source

66
00:05:59.902 --> 00:06:04.448
the most lethal combatants
in all of history.

67
00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:07.284
You're here to fight
each other to the death.

68
00:06:07.367 --> 00:06:09.912
Why should we fight for you?

69
00:06:09.995 --> 00:06:12.206
Our wars are not yet won.

70
00:06:12.289 --> 00:06:14.958
Well. to be transparent.

71
00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:22.883
for our entertainment.

72
00:06:22.966 --> 00:06:24.635
The winner will go back
to his or her time

73
00:06:24.718 --> 00:06:27.179
armed with the knowledge
of their enemies.

74
00:06:27.262 --> 00:06:29.389
and you will be able
to defeat them

75
00:06:29.473 --> 00:06:31.683
because you'll know
their every move.

76
00:06:31.767 --> 00:06:33.644
And how will this
winner be decided?

77
00:06:33.727 --> 00:06:35.813
A fight to the death.

78
00:06:37.523 --> 00:06:39.691
The last one standing wins.

79
00:06:39.775 --> 00:06:43.570
If we die.
does history not change?

80
00:06:43.654 --> 00:06:46.073
No.
It doesn't work like that.

81
00:06:46.156 --> 00:06:48.784
Extractions do not
alter recorded history.

82
00:06:51.286 --> 00:06:53.664
How will I compete?

83
00:06:53.747 --> 00:06:56.583
I can lead armies. but
I have no army here.

84
00:06:56.667 --> 00:06:59.878
and I am not a warrior
skilled in hand-to-hand combat.

85
00:06:59.962 --> 00:07:03.215
I have never killed.
and I will not begin now.

86
00:07:03.298 --> 00:07:05.217
My soul is not to forfeit.

87
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:10.389
You will have intelligence
on all of your competitors.

88
00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:13.725
You all have a very
unique set of skills.

89
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:17.104
and that's what makes
Crimson Havoc so entertaining.

90
00:07:17.187 --> 00:07:19.064
What if you refuse to fight?

91
00:07:19.148 --> 00:07:23.277
If we do not kill.
there will be no victim.

92
00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:27.364
A refuse to fight is a forfeit.

93
00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:30.117
and the penalty is death.

94
00:07:37.541 --> 00:07:41.545
The magic that brought us
here can easily destroy us.

95
00:07:41.628 --> 00:07:44.631
Our legacy might vanish with us.

96
00:07:44.715 --> 00:07:45.799
Put out your arms.

97
00:07:49.344 --> 00:07:51.180
Good choice.

98
00:07:55.601 --> 00:07:57.811
You might feel a little pinch.

99
00:07:57.895 --> 00:08:01.064
These chips that
I'm implanting in your arms

100
00:08:04.359 --> 00:08:06.570
will give you access
to intel on each other.

101
00:08:10.616 --> 00:08:11.950
All the intel is the same.

102
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.541
No one will have
an unfair advantage.

103
00:08:22.586 --> 00:08:24.963
You abducted us. imprisoned us.

104
00:08:25.047 --> 00:08:27.966
and now ask us to
risk our very lives.

105
00:08:28.050 --> 00:08:32.095
How can we trust that this
competition will be fair?

106
00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:34.264
Unfortunately...

107
00:08:36.892 --> 00:08:39.686
You don't
have any other options.

108
00:08:39.770 --> 00:08:43.523
I demand to be
freed immediately.

109
00:08:43.607 --> 00:08:45.150
If I am not released.

110
00:08:45.234 --> 00:08:47.945
you will feel the full
fury of my revenge.

111
00:08:52.574 --> 00:08:56.078
There is only one
path to freedom.

112
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:57.913
and I suggest that you take it.

113
00:09:03.001 --> 00:09:06.004
<i>Crimson Havoc guests.
exit through the doors</i>

114
00:09:06.088 --> 00:09:08.340
<i>and proceed to
the training room.</i>

115
00:09:08.423 --> 00:09:09.424
<i>Good luck.</i>

116
00:09:18.267 --> 00:09:20.102
<i>Welcome to the training room.</i>

117
00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:23.772
<i>The ammunition is live
and the weapons brutal.</i>

118
00:09:23.855 --> 00:09:26.692
<i>Proceed to the chest and
select your instruments.</i>

119
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:28.777
<i>Use this time to prepare.</i>

120
00:09:28.860 --> 00:09:30.153
<i>Good luck.</i>

121
00:10:12.738 --> 00:10:14.281
As resource shortages continue.

122
00:10:14.364 --> 00:10:17.492
Sector 5 officials have
launched the Purity Campaign.

123
00:10:17.576 --> 00:10:19.661
offering ration bonuses
and energy credits.

124
00:10:19.745 --> 00:10:23.290
for tips leading to the arrest
of unregistered individuals.

125
00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:24.791
The world might be gray.

126
00:10:24.875 --> 00:10:27.127
but your view doesn't
have to be.

127
00:10:27.210 --> 00:10:29.796
The new Atmosphera
Neurosynced Vista screen.

128
00:10:29.880 --> 00:10:33.759
the sky is whatever
you want it to be.

129
00:10:33.842 --> 00:10:36.053
In other news.
questions continue to swirl

130
00:10:36.136 --> 00:10:38.388
around the
Temporal Combat Authority.

131
00:10:38.472 --> 00:10:41.892
The TCA is the organization
behind the wildly popular.

132
00:10:41.975 --> 00:10:44.311
Crimson Havoc
Combat tournaments.

133
00:10:44.394 --> 00:10:46.772
To some. it's
the ultimate sport.

134
00:10:46.855 --> 00:10:49.441
To others. the ugliest mirror
of our age.

135
00:10:49.524 --> 00:10:51.193
Wagers soar into the millions.

136
00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:54.363
fortunes are made overnight
and just as easily lost.

137
00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:57.366
Officially. their technology
is sanctioned entertainment.

138
00:10:57.449 --> 00:11:00.077
broadcast to the masses
as cultural unity.

139
00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.621
Unofficially. critics
say thin oversight

140
00:11:02.704 --> 00:11:04.289
and rapid expansion
are concentrating

141
00:11:04.373 --> 00:11:06.625
too much power in private hands.

142
00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:09.669
In a world where food. water.
and energy are scarce.

143
00:11:09.753 --> 00:11:11.380
one thing remains abundant:

144
00:11:11.463 --> 00:11:13.215
The spectacle.

145
00:11:13.298 --> 00:11:15.675
Welcome. sector faithful.

146
00:11:15.759 --> 00:11:17.844
You asked for them.
We brought them back.

147
00:11:17.928 --> 00:11:22.933
Live from the Temporal
Combat Authority Arena.

148
00:11:23.016 --> 00:11:25.352
reborn for your entertainment.

149
00:11:25.435 --> 00:11:31.024
The TCA brings
you Crimson Havoc!

150
00:11:31.108 --> 00:11:35.028
Let's meet the combatants and
put some faces to those odds.

151
00:11:35.112 --> 00:11:37.572
Attila the Hun!

152
00:11:37.656 --> 00:11:39.533
Attila didn't invade. he erased.

153
00:11:39.616 --> 00:11:44.496
A living storm with no mercy.
no borders. and no master.

154
00:11:44.579 --> 00:11:46.331
Oda Nobunaga!

155
00:11:46.415 --> 00:11:47.833
He broke Japan to remake it:

156
00:11:47.916 --> 00:11:50.836
Ruthless. brilliant.
and born for fire.

157
00:11:50.919 --> 00:11:52.963
He conquered tradition
with gunpowder.

158
00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:55.674
strategies. and
unstoppable will.

159
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:58.176
Ghengis Khan!

160
00:11:58.260 --> 00:12:00.095
From exile to emperor.
Khan built

161
00:12:00.178 --> 00:12:02.264
the largest empire in history.

162
00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:06.560
with speed. terror. and
a storm of war behind it.

163
00:12:06.643 --> 00:12:08.603
Shaka Zulu!

164
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:10.355
Turned warriors into weapons.

165
00:12:10.439 --> 00:12:12.149
Shaka redefined battle

166
00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:14.317
with brutal precision.
shaping an empire

167
00:12:14.401 --> 00:12:18.196
with silence. force.
and the edge of a blade.

168
00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:20.699
Queen Hangbe!

169
00:12:20.782 --> 00:12:22.534
Hangbe led without fanfare.

170
00:12:22.617 --> 00:12:24.619
birthing an army
of warrior women

171
00:12:24.703 --> 00:12:26.746
that would echo
throughout history.

172
00:12:26.830 --> 00:12:28.290
Boudica!

173
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:29.373
They took her crown.

174
00:12:29.416 --> 00:12:31.293
so she burned their city.

175
00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:33.753
Boudica rose from ruin
to lead a bloody revolt

176
00:12:33.837 --> 00:12:35.922
against the might of Rome.

177
00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:38.133
Mama Huaco!

178
00:12:38.216 --> 00:12:39.843
Warrior matriarch!

179
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:42.929
She was the first queen
and the fiercest.

180
00:12:43.013 --> 00:12:45.640
Huaco protected her people
with sling. mace.

181
00:12:45.724 --> 00:12:48.226
and mountain-born range.

182
00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:50.020
Joan of Arc!

183
00:12:50.103 --> 00:12:52.481
Led by visions. feared by kings.

184
00:12:52.564 --> 00:12:55.150
Joan marched through fire
with divine fury.

185
00:12:55.233 --> 00:12:58.904
a teenage girl
who commanded armies and won.

186
00:12:58.987 --> 00:13:00.530
Cleopatra.

187
00:13:00.614 --> 00:13:03.450
Not just beauty. cunning. charm.

188
00:13:03.533 --> 00:13:05.869
and command. the final
queen of Egypt

189
00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:08.205
and the deadliest
diplomat of her time.

190
00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:15.629
And?

191
00:13:15.712 --> 00:13:17.130
Intense.

192
00:13:17.214 --> 00:13:18.232
I don't think I can
do that again.

193
00:13:18.256 --> 00:13:19.508
Well. you will.

194
00:13:19.591 --> 00:13:21.027
You only have over
a billion reasons.

195
00:13:21.051 --> 00:13:22.719
Hmm.

196
00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:24.071
Do you have all
the investors lined up?

197
00:13:24.095 --> 00:13:25.597
Yeah.

198
00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:27.520
All you gotta do is
sit back. relax. and watch.

199
00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:29.518
Moment of truth.

200
00:13:29.601 --> 00:13:32.479
<i>Good evening. investors
and distinguished patrons.</i>

201
00:13:32.562 --> 00:13:34.731
<i>We present for your purchase.</i>

202
00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:37.776
<i>Evaluate their strength
and envision their place</i>

203
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:43.698
<i>in your collection. your state.
or your command.</i>

204
00:13:43.782 --> 00:13:48.203
I should kill you now and
put you out of your misery.

205
00:13:48.286 --> 00:13:51.998
I am afraid I am not much
with weapons of death.

206
00:13:52.082 --> 00:13:54.292
They have not chosen well.

207
00:13:54.376 --> 00:13:58.296
We have all been chosen
for a reason.

208
00:13:58.380 --> 00:14:01.424
It is a test from our Lord.

209
00:14:01.508 --> 00:14:04.803
If that is true.
then it is a cruel one.

210
00:14:04.886 --> 00:14:07.847
There must be a way for
us to free ourselves

211
00:14:07.931 --> 00:14:09.558
and get back home.

212
00:14:09.641 --> 00:14:13.353
Perhaps the way is
to work together.

213
00:14:13.436 --> 00:14:15.981
It might be the only
key to survival.

214
00:14:21.319 --> 00:14:24.656
Well. the three of us have
great leadership skills.

215
00:14:24.739 --> 00:14:27.284
So does Cleopatra.

216
00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:31.621
She doesn't seem to be
interested in joining us.

217
00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:35.959
If we are forced to fight.
I can defend you both.

218
00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:40.213
The gods favor the bold
and the divine.

219
00:14:40.297 --> 00:14:43.883
We must win everyone to
our cause. or we are lost.

220
00:14:45.594 --> 00:14:46.928
Listen!

221
00:14:49.306 --> 00:14:52.142
My name is Joan.

222
00:14:52.225 --> 00:14:55.020
Attila. Mama. and
I have a proposal.

223
00:14:55.103 --> 00:14:56.521
We're not interested. Joan.

224
00:15:01.443 --> 00:15:04.362
I do not know why
I was brought here.

225
00:15:04.446 --> 00:15:07.907
Maybe it's God's will or
the devil's artifice.

226
00:15:07.991 --> 00:15:12.662
I must believe
there is another way.

227
00:15:12.746 --> 00:15:15.790
If one can be sent home.
so can all.

228
00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:17.667
Only if you win.

229
00:15:23.757 --> 00:15:25.550
We spoke of this.

230
00:15:25.634 --> 00:15:29.137
The strong survive.
nothing more.

231
00:15:29.220 --> 00:15:31.931
Then they erred
when they gathered us.

232
00:15:32.015 --> 00:15:36.186
We will slaughter our captors.
and we will find our way home.

233
00:15:38.480 --> 00:15:41.983
Why risk all the blood shed?

234
00:15:42.067 --> 00:15:44.361
Why not try something
else first?

235
00:15:52.827 --> 00:15:55.955
The people who kidnapped us
made that choice for us.

236
00:15:56.039 --> 00:15:57.415
We will destroy them

237
00:15:57.499 --> 00:15:59.584
and make sure it never
happens to anyone else.

238
00:15:59.668 --> 00:16:00.835
It seems like our cue.

239
00:16:03.088 --> 00:16:04.923
- Ready?
- Ready.

240
00:16:05.006 --> 00:16:06.883
Let the games begin.

241
00:16:10.011 --> 00:16:14.224
We must act with reason.
not rage.

242
00:16:14.307 --> 00:16:15.392
If we turn...

243
00:16:15.475 --> 00:16:16.475
Silence!

244
00:16:17.477 --> 00:16:18.520
What's that?

245
00:16:18.603 --> 00:16:19.771
Poison.

246
00:16:22.524 --> 00:16:24.192
[coughing]

247
00:17:25.754 --> 00:17:26.754
Wait!

248
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:28.006
We have no choice.

249
00:17:32.969 --> 00:17:35.013
Ladies and gentlemen.
our first fight.

250
00:17:35.096 --> 00:17:36.681
Boudica
vs. Ghengis Khan.

251
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:46.191
[struggling]

252
00:17:59.496 --> 00:18:01.164
[grunting]

253
00:18:07.253 --> 00:18:09.964
Please stop fighting each other!

254
00:18:10.048 --> 00:18:11.424
We have a common cause.

255
00:18:14.135 --> 00:18:15.637
No!

256
00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:19.349
No. I beg of you.
Stop this.

257
00:18:19.432 --> 00:18:22.644
There is no cause but survival.

258
00:18:22.727 --> 00:18:24.020
Boudica. run!

259
00:18:27.899 --> 00:18:28.959
She better run back to France.

260
00:18:28.983 --> 00:18:30.902
Ghengis Khan vs.
Joan of Arc.

261
00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:50.671
Do not move.

262
00:18:53.299 --> 00:18:55.927
I will not rest until
all of you are dead.

263
00:18:56.010 --> 00:18:57.345
[gunshot]

264
00:19:03.059 --> 00:19:04.519
Oh. conquest denied.

265
00:19:04.602 --> 00:19:05.854
Empire offline.

266
00:19:13.486 --> 00:19:15.196
Thank you.

267
00:19:15.280 --> 00:19:17.407
But why did you save me?

268
00:19:17.490 --> 00:19:19.659
You speak truth.

269
00:19:19.742 --> 00:19:22.662
I trust you to lead us out...
Alive.

270
00:19:25.373 --> 00:19:26.499
I will try my best.

271
00:19:32.297 --> 00:19:33.673
I wish it hadn't come to that.

272
00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:36.467
As do I.

273
00:19:36.968 --> 00:19:38.511
But he would have
killed us both.

274
00:19:48.897 --> 00:19:50.982
May the souls of
the faithfully departed

275
00:19:51.065 --> 00:19:52.650
through the mercy of
God rest in peace.

276
00:19:52.734 --> 00:19:54.027
Amen.

277
00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.530
[servos whirring]

278
00:20:00.658 --> 00:20:03.286
[sound rising]

279
00:20:03.369 --> 00:20:04.829
Where is that sound coming from?

280
00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:12.795
This is no ordinary battle.

281
00:20:12.879 --> 00:20:14.148
There must be more
they're not telling us.

282
00:20:14.172 --> 00:20:15.924
We have to find the others.

283
00:20:16.007 --> 00:20:19.344
Convince them that we
need to fight together.

284
00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:21.747
I have loved ones that I am
determined to get back home to.

285
00:21:11.229 --> 00:21:12.313
Lead on.

286
00:21:16.317 --> 00:21:17.485
Let's hear it. Sectors.

287
00:21:17.568 --> 00:21:20.446
Our first fight
and our first kill.

288
00:21:20.530 --> 00:21:22.073
Oda Nobunaga doesn't waste time

289
00:21:22.156 --> 00:21:24.784
burning his one shot
right out of the gate.

290
00:21:24.867 --> 00:21:27.704
And Boudica took a nasty
slice but limped out alive.

291
00:21:27.787 --> 00:21:29.014
Let's look at the leader board.

292
00:21:29.038 --> 00:21:31.541
Well. well. our first alliance.

293
00:21:31.624 --> 00:21:34.502
Joan of Arc couldn't rally the
combatants in the training room.

294
00:21:34.585 --> 00:21:36.462
but clearly Oda sees
something in her.

295
00:21:36.546 --> 00:21:38.715
How long will she hold out
without drawing blood?

296
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:41.759
Is it strategy or stubbornness?

297
00:21:41.843 --> 00:21:44.679
And is Oda her protector or
is he just waiting

298
00:21:44.762 --> 00:21:46.681
for the right moment
to stab the blade in?

299
00:21:54.731 --> 00:21:58.234
Oh. no. no!

300
00:21:58.317 --> 00:21:59.317
Take a breath.

301
00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:03.489
I'm dead.

302
00:22:03.573 --> 00:22:06.451
No. no. you're alive.

303
00:22:06.534 --> 00:22:10.955
Oh great Khan.
supreme ruler of the Mongols.

304
00:22:11.039 --> 00:22:12.915
You're a mighty warrior.

305
00:22:12.999 --> 00:22:16.335
You're a strong warrior.

306
00:22:17.295 --> 00:22:19.172
But it's time for you to rest.

307
00:22:21.215 --> 00:22:22.759
[speaking Middle Mongolian]

308
00:22:36.564 --> 00:22:37.690
What did you say to him?

309
00:22:39.525 --> 00:22:42.236
Your fight is done.
Your soul rides free.

310
00:22:42.320 --> 00:22:45.490
And you just happen
to know ancient Mongolian?

311
00:22:45.573 --> 00:22:47.992
You guys. if we don't
respect their history.

312
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:49.356
then all of this is meaningless.

313
00:22:50.453 --> 00:22:51.788
Yeah. Leon.

314
00:22:51.871 --> 00:22:55.041
Yeah. but...
Come on. ancient Mongolian?

315
00:22:55.124 --> 00:22:56.644
Just make sure the white room
is ready.

316
00:23:21.859 --> 00:23:24.695
This all looks familiar.

317
00:23:24.779 --> 00:23:26.531
I've seen that
fallen log before.

318
00:23:29.325 --> 00:23:30.368
Let us stop for a moment.

319
00:23:31.869 --> 00:23:34.622
I will climb for a better view.

320
00:23:34.705 --> 00:23:37.750
Perhaps I will be able
to spot the others.

321
00:23:37.834 --> 00:23:40.962
Or at least find our bearings.
These woods are a labyrinth.

322
00:23:42.088 --> 00:23:43.131
I shall keep watch.

323
00:23:58.229 --> 00:23:59.438
[gasps]

324
00:24:03.025 --> 00:24:04.025
Show yourself!

325
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:08.656
It's you.

326
00:24:08.739 --> 00:24:10.408
You nearly struck me.

327
00:24:10.491 --> 00:24:12.910
I thought you were the others.

328
00:24:12.994 --> 00:24:16.080
When we woke up.
chaos broke out.

329
00:24:16.164 --> 00:24:18.541
Some had already
formed alliances.

330
00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:21.502
And I fought free and
fled for my own survival.

331
00:24:22.712 --> 00:24:24.922
How far did you come?

332
00:24:25.006 --> 00:24:27.008
Not too far. but I'm unsure.

333
00:24:29.051 --> 00:24:30.636
Well. join us.

334
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:35.016
If we unite. we stand a chance.
It's the only way.

335
00:24:35.099 --> 00:24:37.351
You have my word. Joan.
I keep my promises.

336
00:24:38.477 --> 00:24:39.562
Wait.

337
00:24:47.737 --> 00:24:49.322
I will fight at your side.

338
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:52.617
Have you seen Mama?

339
00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:54.869
She was there when I first woke.

340
00:24:54.952 --> 00:24:57.872
But she vanished
after the fighting.

341
00:24:57.955 --> 00:24:59.999
I thought I spotted her
just ahead in the clearing.

342
00:25:01.834 --> 00:25:05.379
But then I heard you coming
and lost sight of her.

343
00:25:05.463 --> 00:25:07.298
She might not be far.
We should head that way.

344
00:25:08.466 --> 00:25:09.717
I will scout ahead.

345
00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:10.927
No. wait!

346
00:25:12.136 --> 00:25:13.512
Stay close.

347
00:25:13.596 --> 00:25:15.431
If we separate.
we are easy prey.

348
00:25:15.514 --> 00:25:18.100
No one will see me.

349
00:25:18.184 --> 00:25:19.424
But I will keep within earshot.

350
00:25:55.221 --> 00:25:56.430
[grunts]

351
00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:16.742
She found the plants.

352
00:26:16.826 --> 00:26:19.287
I see that.
So do the buyers.

353
00:26:19.370 --> 00:26:20.621
Her value is already rising.

354
00:26:51.068 --> 00:26:52.820
I don't see anybody.

355
00:26:52.903 --> 00:26:55.656
Attila said they weren't far.
so they must be close.

356
00:27:02.872 --> 00:27:04.123
[twig breaks]

357
00:27:04.206 --> 00:27:06.125
There.

358
00:27:06.208 --> 00:27:07.209
Somebody approaches.

359
00:27:14.925 --> 00:27:17.011
Mama!

360
00:27:17.094 --> 00:27:20.348
Joan. I'm so relieved it's you.

361
00:27:20.431 --> 00:27:22.183
Attila just came through

362
00:27:22.266 --> 00:27:24.977
and he said he'd scout
to make sure it was safe.

363
00:27:25.061 --> 00:27:27.605
Oda?

364
00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:30.775
We're allies now?

365
00:27:30.858 --> 00:27:31.858
Joan has my trust.

366
00:27:33.235 --> 00:27:35.029
He's with us.

367
00:27:35.112 --> 00:27:38.407
We're looking for the others
in hopes to unite everyone.

368
00:27:38.491 --> 00:27:41.327
I think that might be
harder than you expect.

369
00:27:41.410 --> 00:27:44.789
Everybody woke up and thought
violence was their only path.

370
00:27:44.872 --> 00:27:48.250
Everybody was trying to
kill one another violently.

371
00:27:48.334 --> 00:27:50.669
I tried to stop it.
but for my own safety.

372
00:27:50.753 --> 00:27:53.672
I fled to find you.

373
00:27:53.756 --> 00:27:56.050
We saw the same thing
with Genghis Khan.

374
00:27:56.133 --> 00:27:57.426
Oda saved me.

375
00:27:59.345 --> 00:28:00.513
He had to kill.

376
00:28:02.139 --> 00:28:03.139
But there was no choice.

377
00:28:05.101 --> 00:28:08.104
Here. Eat.

378
00:28:08.187 --> 00:28:10.439
You must be hungry.

379
00:28:10.523 --> 00:28:12.066
I found this not too far away.

380
00:28:35.131 --> 00:28:36.382
Thank you. Mama.

381
00:28:38.843 --> 00:28:39.843
Thank you for sharing.

382
00:28:56.402 --> 00:29:00.739
Three-way Throwdown. Shaka Zulu
vs. Boudica vs. Queen Hangbe.

383
00:29:00.823 --> 00:29:02.491
[grunting. shouting]

384
00:29:20.759 --> 00:29:21.844
Stop at once!

385
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:25.222
What would you have us do?

386
00:29:25.306 --> 00:29:26.891
You're not the boss!

387
00:29:26.974 --> 00:29:29.435
Every fighter for themselves.
last man standing!

388
00:29:29.518 --> 00:29:30.936
And the rest dead!

389
00:29:31.020 --> 00:29:33.189
Or we could change the rules.

390
00:29:33.272 --> 00:29:34.940
If we were to make a pact now.

391
00:29:35.024 --> 00:29:37.902
the four of us can ensure
we're the last remaining.

392
00:29:37.985 --> 00:29:39.612
Together. we are unstoppable.

393
00:29:41.280 --> 00:29:43.324
Why should we trust you?

394
00:29:43.407 --> 00:29:46.368
The three of us are much
stronger and skillful.

395
00:29:46.452 --> 00:29:48.871
We could kill you and
be the final three.

396
00:29:50.706 --> 00:29:52.583
You are strong. yes.

397
00:29:52.666 --> 00:29:55.419
But strength alone
does not win wars.

398
00:29:55.503 --> 00:29:58.130
With my cunning and your power.

399
00:29:58.214 --> 00:30:00.883
none could stand in our way.

400
00:30:00.966 --> 00:30:05.221
Together. we can
defeat our captors.

401
00:30:05.304 --> 00:30:09.934
But first. we must get rid
of Joan and the others.

402
00:30:10.017 --> 00:30:13.270
Their mercy is a weakness
we cannot afford.

403
00:30:15.523 --> 00:30:16.523
Release me.

404
00:30:23.447 --> 00:30:25.074
That is a smart plan.

405
00:30:25.157 --> 00:30:27.326
But hear me!

406
00:30:27.409 --> 00:30:30.496
When only we four remain.
I will show no mercy!

407
00:30:30.579 --> 00:30:32.373
Nor will I!

408
00:30:32.456 --> 00:30:35.834
I would not expect anything less
from warriors such as you.

409
00:30:40.297 --> 00:30:41.297
I'll do my part.

410
00:30:43.884 --> 00:30:44.927
Look out!

411
00:30:46.845 --> 00:30:48.180
Are you hurt?

412
00:30:48.264 --> 00:30:49.974
I am not.

413
00:30:50.057 --> 00:30:51.058
[grunts]

414
00:30:53.727 --> 00:30:57.106
Shaka. Hangbe. go!
Find the archer!

415
00:31:08.117 --> 00:31:09.368
[grunting]

416
00:31:16.125 --> 00:31:21.213
The pain will fade.
and the wound will heal.

417
00:31:25.926 --> 00:31:27.219
Oh. what have we here?

418
00:31:27.303 --> 00:31:28.929
Shaka Zulu and Queen Hangbe

419
00:31:29.013 --> 00:31:31.265
versus Attila the Hun
and Oda Nobunaga.

420
00:31:32.391 --> 00:31:33.642
[grunting]

421
00:31:48.741 --> 00:31:49.908
Don't move.

422
00:31:49.992 --> 00:31:51.410
Free us or kill us!

423
00:31:51.493 --> 00:31:54.955
We will not be your prisoners.

424
00:31:55.039 --> 00:31:56.040
We got two of them.

425
00:31:56.123 --> 00:31:57.625
Hold on. let me speak to them.

426
00:31:57.708 --> 00:31:59.460
Free us or kill us.

427
00:31:59.543 --> 00:32:01.295
We are not your enemies.

428
00:32:01.378 --> 00:32:05.382
If we keep fighting.
we all lose.

429
00:32:05.466 --> 00:32:08.385
Khan is already dead. and
he vanished before our eyes.

430
00:32:08.469 --> 00:32:10.387
Something unnatural is at work.

431
00:32:10.471 --> 00:32:12.765
You are not to be trusted.

432
00:32:12.848 --> 00:32:14.767
What would I gain by lying?

433
00:32:22.358 --> 00:32:24.068
Move or draw your weapon.

434
00:32:26.028 --> 00:32:28.739
We do not want any
more blood spilled today.

435
00:32:30.157 --> 00:32:31.325
Join us.

436
00:32:37.247 --> 00:32:38.791
Joan. be careful.

437
00:32:38.874 --> 00:32:40.167
It's all right.

438
00:32:40.250 --> 00:32:41.794
We need to trust each other.

439
00:32:43.379 --> 00:32:45.464
Start by trusting me.

440
00:32:47.383 --> 00:32:48.509
[grunting]

441
00:32:50.719 --> 00:32:53.138
Rock beat royalty.
the Queen is dead.

442
00:32:58.602 --> 00:33:00.604
Attila! Attila!

443
00:33:02.439 --> 00:33:04.650
- I'll hunt him down.
- Leave him for now.

444
00:33:04.733 --> 00:33:07.361
One less enemy.

445
00:33:07.444 --> 00:33:10.906
We are not here to kill people.

446
00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:13.701
We are here to survive
and to free us all.

447
00:33:13.784 --> 00:33:15.703
[sound rising]

448
00:33:15.786 --> 00:33:17.371
That sound.

449
00:33:17.454 --> 00:33:21.208
Queen Hangbe goes with Khan.

450
00:33:21.291 --> 00:33:23.460
This is the work of the devil.

451
00:33:27.005 --> 00:33:28.590
By all the gods in the sky.

452
00:33:43.731 --> 00:33:46.650
This isn't holy.

453
00:33:46.734 --> 00:33:48.610
This is more trickery.

454
00:33:48.694 --> 00:33:52.114
Look around you.
This is no battlefield.

455
00:33:52.197 --> 00:33:55.159
We're not fighting
for honor or a country.

456
00:33:55.242 --> 00:33:58.036
We're pieces on a board

457
00:33:58.120 --> 00:34:00.456
moved for
someone else's amusement.

458
00:34:02.750 --> 00:34:04.376
Like a child's toy.

459
00:34:04.460 --> 00:34:07.463
And children are careless
with their toys.

460
00:34:11.842 --> 00:34:13.343
Chaos in the North Quadrant.

461
00:34:13.427 --> 00:34:15.262
Attila almost hit
Joan with an arrow.

462
00:34:15.345 --> 00:34:18.140
but he didn't miss Boudica.
That's her second wound.

463
00:34:18.223 --> 00:34:19.617
Let's take a look
at the leader board.

464
00:34:19.641 --> 00:34:21.281
Across the field.
we had a three-way brawl

465
00:34:21.351 --> 00:34:22.519
broken up by Cleopatra.

466
00:34:22.603 --> 00:34:25.564
No steel. no shield.
Just words.

467
00:34:25.647 --> 00:34:26.940
Now they stand together.

468
00:34:27.024 --> 00:34:28.400
A second alliance is born:

469
00:34:28.484 --> 00:34:30.694
One built on
calculated persuasion.

470
00:34:30.778 --> 00:34:33.739
The other on conviction
and strategy.

471
00:34:33.822 --> 00:34:37.743
The question is.
who survives the night?

472
00:34:37.826 --> 00:34:39.095
Mama Huaco's strike
punched a hole

473
00:34:39.119 --> 00:34:40.662
in Cleopatra's alliance.

474
00:34:40.746 --> 00:34:42.015
For the queen. it's
the end of the line.

475
00:34:42.039 --> 00:34:43.582
Claimed by the arena.

476
00:34:43.665 --> 00:34:45.584
Returned to the age
from which she came.

477
00:34:50.047 --> 00:34:51.381
She restrained?

478
00:34:51.465 --> 00:34:52.674
Mm-hmm.

479
00:34:52.758 --> 00:34:54.038
Okay. good. now get out of here.

480
00:35:01.350 --> 00:35:03.018
<i>She ready?</i>

481
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:04.645
Getting there.

482
00:35:06.563 --> 00:35:09.358
How is your shoulder?

483
00:35:09.441 --> 00:35:11.193
Much better.

484
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:12.694
You have my thanks.

485
00:35:14.738 --> 00:35:17.699
We are stronger together.

486
00:35:17.783 --> 00:35:21.453
When we find Attila. he's mine.

487
00:35:21.537 --> 00:35:24.873
As you desire. but do not be
too consumed by your wrath.

488
00:35:24.957 --> 00:35:28.418
We must be rid of all of them
if we wish to return.

489
00:35:28.502 --> 00:35:31.880
I have grown tired of you
telling me what to do.

490
00:35:31.964 --> 00:35:33.173
Why should I listen to someone

491
00:35:33.257 --> 00:35:35.759
who has never fought
for her life?

492
00:35:35.843 --> 00:35:39.721
I am a king.
I lead from the front.

493
00:35:39.805 --> 00:35:44.142
When I find Attila. I will
rip his heart out myself.

494
00:35:53.819 --> 00:35:56.029
The others have
passed through here.

495
00:35:56.113 --> 00:35:57.114
Footprints.

496
00:35:58.490 --> 00:35:59.616
They are not far.

497
00:36:11.169 --> 00:36:12.504
There. look ahead.

498
00:36:12.588 --> 00:36:14.798
That must be where
our captors hide.

499
00:36:14.882 --> 00:36:17.092
or perhaps where they hide
those who disappear.

500
00:36:24.308 --> 00:36:25.475
We're being followed.

501
00:36:25.559 --> 00:36:27.227
Then we move faster.

502
00:36:27.311 --> 00:36:28.687
Or we wait for them.

503
00:36:28.770 --> 00:36:31.148
If we unite. we stand
a better chance inside.

504
00:36:31.231 --> 00:36:33.650
Whatever is killing
the dead must be stopped.

505
00:36:33.734 --> 00:36:35.068
They won't talk.

506
00:36:35.152 --> 00:36:36.737
They want blood.

507
00:36:36.820 --> 00:36:38.697
I'll stay behind
and ambush them.

508
00:36:38.780 --> 00:36:40.616
You three. go ahead.

509
00:36:40.699 --> 00:36:42.951
No. We stay together.

510
00:36:43.035 --> 00:36:45.078
Now that we know they're coming.

511
00:36:45.162 --> 00:36:47.414
we can catch them
and convince them.

512
00:36:47.497 --> 00:36:48.832
And if they refuse?

513
00:36:49.958 --> 00:36:51.919
Then we move on.

514
00:36:52.002 --> 00:36:54.379
But I know they will not
unite if they are dead.

515
00:36:54.463 --> 00:36:56.882
Or worse.

516
00:36:56.965 --> 00:36:58.759
Let's get into position
for when they come.

517
00:36:58.842 --> 00:37:00.886
Oda. you take the high ground?

518
00:37:00.969 --> 00:37:02.763
The rest of us will
spread out and wait.

519
00:37:09.353 --> 00:37:11.605
Shaka. I must speak with you.

520
00:37:11.688 --> 00:37:13.565
No time.

521
00:37:13.649 --> 00:37:15.108
You two keep pace with me.

522
00:37:15.192 --> 00:37:16.652
Otherwise we will
never catch them.

523
00:37:18.195 --> 00:37:19.988
What's he doing now?

524
00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:23.617
- Let's go.
- Wait.

525
00:37:23.700 --> 00:37:25.577
I do not believe
it would be this simple.

526
00:37:32.501 --> 00:37:33.585
[shouts]

527
00:37:37.464 --> 00:37:39.341
Shaka Zulu versus Oda Nobunaga.

528
00:37:42.719 --> 00:37:43.637
[grunting]

529
00:37:43.720 --> 00:37:44.972
We need to help.

530
00:37:45.055 --> 00:37:46.055
Stay hidden.

531
00:37:46.098 --> 00:37:49.059
Rushing in means certain death.

532
00:37:49.142 --> 00:37:50.268
[grunting]

533
00:38:05.951 --> 00:38:07.536
We don't want to kill you.

534
00:38:07.619 --> 00:38:09.037
Please reconsider.

535
00:38:09.121 --> 00:38:12.249
We need to every fighter.

536
00:38:12.332 --> 00:38:13.417
Do you submit?

537
00:38:13.500 --> 00:38:15.002
Never.

538
00:38:15.085 --> 00:38:16.461
Reconsider.

539
00:38:16.545 --> 00:38:18.338
Please.

540
00:38:21.133 --> 00:38:22.133
[shouts]

541
00:38:23.593 --> 00:38:24.761
[grunting]

542
00:38:27.180 --> 00:38:29.474
Oh. Shaka drops.

543
00:38:29.558 --> 00:38:30.892
Oda still stands.

544
00:38:36.231 --> 00:38:37.315
No...

545
00:38:43.947 --> 00:38:45.365
No. there is always another way.

546
00:38:45.449 --> 00:38:46.449
No!

547
00:38:48.076 --> 00:38:50.912
If he had not turned on us now.
he would later.

548
00:38:59.212 --> 00:39:00.338
[grunts]

549
00:39:21.693 --> 00:39:24.279
<i>Shaka. sit back down.
A tech is one the way.</i>

550
00:39:24.362 --> 00:39:25.405
Free me!

551
00:39:32.454 --> 00:39:34.915
Say what you will. but
they build a mighty fortress.

552
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:40.295
Even the hardest stone crumbles.

553
00:39:56.812 --> 00:39:57.813
I have found something.

554
00:40:11.451 --> 00:40:13.161
Save your sword.
Master Nobunaga.

555
00:40:15.122 --> 00:40:16.790
This fortress is
not of our time.

556
00:40:16.873 --> 00:40:18.083
Our ways don't work here.

557
00:40:19.584 --> 00:40:20.919
Yet I have destroyed many.

558
00:40:22.212 --> 00:40:24.381
Well. this is unexpected.

559
00:40:24.464 --> 00:40:26.508
Four combatants Oda Nobunaga.
Joan of Arc.

560
00:40:26.591 --> 00:40:28.552
Attila the Hun and Mama Huaco

561
00:40:28.635 --> 00:40:31.138
heading straight for
the TCA fortress walls.

562
00:40:31.221 --> 00:40:32.764
For those of you
new to the game.

563
00:40:32.848 --> 00:40:34.474
this is a restricted zone.

564
00:40:34.558 --> 00:40:36.351
You don't storm the castle
in Crimson Havoc.

565
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:38.770
But the TCA has made sure
those gates are guarded.

566
00:40:38.854 --> 00:40:39.854
Let's get back in there.

567
00:40:41.148 --> 00:40:42.315
Shh...

568
00:40:42.399 --> 00:40:43.316
[rumbling]

569
00:40:43.400 --> 00:40:44.401
There's a sound.

570
00:40:46.820 --> 00:40:50.782
<i>Attention fighters. you are
entering a restricted area.</i>

571
00:40:50.866 --> 00:40:53.535
<i>Please return to the
combat zone immediately.</i>

572
00:40:53.618 --> 00:40:55.120
Birds that talk?

573
00:40:57.789 --> 00:40:59.708
<i>Attila. put your weapon down.</i>

574
00:40:59.791 --> 00:41:01.626
<i>Any interference with our drones</i>

575
00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:03.753
<i>will be considered
an act of aggression.</i>

576
00:41:03.837 --> 00:41:07.382
<i>Our retaliation will be swift.</i>

577
00:41:07.465 --> 00:41:08.505
<i>Thank you for your coop...</i>

578
00:41:09.843 --> 00:41:10.844
Damn it.

579
00:41:10.927 --> 00:41:12.512
Well. we warned them.

580
00:41:19.853 --> 00:41:21.688
What are they doing?

581
00:41:21.771 --> 00:41:23.356
Spread out. take cover.

582
00:41:30.614 --> 00:41:31.698
Mama. your slingshot.

583
00:41:40.248 --> 00:41:41.333
[shouts]

584
00:41:45.837 --> 00:41:47.047
[shouts]

585
00:41:54.596 --> 00:41:56.514
Your god favors you.

586
00:42:00.060 --> 00:42:01.770
Their weapons are powerful.

587
00:42:03.480 --> 00:42:05.857
Have you been badly injured?

588
00:42:05.941 --> 00:42:07.275
I'll survive.

589
00:42:12.405 --> 00:42:13.949
<i>Operator detected.</i>

590
00:42:14.032 --> 00:42:15.784
<i>Weapon gyroscope damaged.</i>

591
00:42:15.867 --> 00:42:20.372
<i>Engage rear triggers
for manual override.</i>

592
00:42:20.455 --> 00:42:21.455
- Oh!
- [gunfire]

593
00:42:23.833 --> 00:42:25.877
Joan. what have you found?

594
00:42:28.922 --> 00:42:30.966
I think I just found our way in.

595
00:42:33.635 --> 00:42:34.970
[gunfire]

596
00:42:44.437 --> 00:42:46.856
[grunts]

597
00:43:04.457 --> 00:43:05.875
[grunting]

598
00:43:07.127 --> 00:43:08.169
[shouting]

599
00:43:17.512 --> 00:43:18.596
[alarm sounds]

600
00:43:22.934 --> 00:43:23.935
Clever.

601
00:43:24.019 --> 00:43:26.062
How's the queen doing?

602
00:43:27.856 --> 00:43:29.941
AI cerebral upload
seems to hold.

603
00:43:30.025 --> 00:43:31.025
She's good to go.

604
00:43:32.986 --> 00:43:35.405
Activate subjects
A and B please.

605
00:43:35.488 --> 00:43:37.532
Keep all translators on.

606
00:43:37.615 --> 00:43:39.075
Make it interesting.

607
00:43:40.869 --> 00:43:41.869
How confident are we?

608
00:43:43.371 --> 00:43:44.748
Very.

609
00:43:56.134 --> 00:43:57.927
Move or be moved.

610
00:43:59.929 --> 00:44:03.475
Shaka Zulu versus Genghis Khan
and Queen Hangbe.

611
00:44:03.558 --> 00:44:04.768
Attack.

612
00:44:07.812 --> 00:44:09.230
[grunting]

613
00:44:18.490 --> 00:44:20.116
Stand down.

614
00:44:20.200 --> 00:44:21.576
Let her pass.

615
00:44:29.376 --> 00:44:30.960
<i>Let's take him to
the surgical theater.</i>

616
00:44:31.044 --> 00:44:33.421
- More adjusting?
- Yeah.

617
00:44:33.505 --> 00:44:35.507
No lag.
I like that.

618
00:44:35.590 --> 00:44:38.551
Maybe we need to make
the attacks more relentless.

619
00:44:38.635 --> 00:44:40.178
The impact readings
are a little low.

620
00:44:40.261 --> 00:44:41.513
so let's increase it.

621
00:44:41.596 --> 00:44:43.264
Yes. sir.

622
00:44:43.348 --> 00:44:45.809
I will let the investors know.

623
00:44:45.892 --> 00:44:48.311
Even at this rate. we can
increase our demand by 30%.

624
00:44:51.981 --> 00:44:56.653
We've just lost visuals on
Oda Nobunaga. Attila the Han.

625
00:44:56.736 --> 00:44:58.571
Mama Huaco and Joan of Arc.

626
00:44:58.655 --> 00:44:59.989
If you're just joining us.

627
00:45:00.073 --> 00:45:02.575
our four combatants
blasted their way

628
00:45:02.659 --> 00:45:05.120
into a maintenance hatch

629
00:45:05.203 --> 00:45:08.373
and are now off camera.

630
00:45:08.456 --> 00:45:12.377
This looks like it
goes on for miles.

631
00:45:12.460 --> 00:45:14.629
You truly believe
they are down here?

632
00:45:14.712 --> 00:45:16.047
We have to keep moving.

633
00:45:16.131 --> 00:45:17.799
There must be something.

634
00:45:17.882 --> 00:45:21.344
They want to stay hidden.
We'll never find them.

635
00:45:21.428 --> 00:45:23.012
Have faith.

636
00:45:23.096 --> 00:45:25.432
I have faith in myself.

637
00:45:25.515 --> 00:45:28.351
I've already killed
two other fighters.

638
00:45:28.435 --> 00:45:31.104
They assembled great warriors.

639
00:45:31.187 --> 00:45:32.939
but I'm the greatest.

640
00:45:33.022 --> 00:45:35.900
I'm going to win this
Crimson Havoc

641
00:45:35.984 --> 00:45:37.360
and go back to my time.

642
00:45:38.862 --> 00:45:41.531
Oda. stay with us.

643
00:45:41.614 --> 00:45:45.910
You only want me to stay
because you know you can't win.

644
00:45:45.994 --> 00:45:49.581
I won't attack you until
there are no other options.

645
00:45:49.664 --> 00:45:53.877
And if you find these people.
I will help you.

646
00:45:53.960 --> 00:45:59.382
But for now. I am going to find
and kill Boudica and Cleopatra.

647
00:45:59.466 --> 00:46:01.634
They're most certainly
plotting to kill all of us.

648
00:46:01.718 --> 00:46:03.761
Oda. you're being reckless.

649
00:46:03.845 --> 00:46:07.432
Don't leave us.
We need to stick together.

650
00:46:07.515 --> 00:46:08.516
I will see you again.

651
00:46:12.187 --> 00:46:13.187
Oda. wait.

652
00:46:27.160 --> 00:46:28.828
Should we go after him?

653
00:46:28.912 --> 00:46:31.331
Yes. but first we must find
Joan and the others.

654
00:46:34.250 --> 00:46:35.530
You'll have to do it without me.

655
00:46:37.045 --> 00:46:39.797
The pain is spreading
through my body.

656
00:46:39.881 --> 00:46:42.759
My vision seems to be
getting blurred.

657
00:46:42.842 --> 00:46:45.553
You look unwell.

658
00:46:45.637 --> 00:46:48.431
It must be something
our captors have done to you.

659
00:46:49.557 --> 00:46:50.934
Stay strong.

660
00:46:51.017 --> 00:46:52.777
We will find them and
get you feeling better.

661
00:46:54.771 --> 00:46:55.939
This will help for now.

662
00:47:01.694 --> 00:47:02.694
[groans]

663
00:47:18.169 --> 00:47:20.088
You are playing with us.

664
00:47:21.422 --> 00:47:22.422
No.

665
00:47:26.553 --> 00:47:29.889
Please. kill me now.

666
00:47:34.644 --> 00:47:38.106
The mighty Zulu King who
galvanized his whole country?

667
00:47:38.189 --> 00:47:39.482
You want to give up now?

668
00:47:41.859 --> 00:47:43.903
I know what I am fighting for.

669
00:47:45.905 --> 00:47:49.117
I am fighting for
the freedom of my people.

670
00:47:50.660 --> 00:47:52.495
Fighting for my nation.

671
00:47:54.497 --> 00:47:58.001
But here. in this place

672
00:47:59.752 --> 00:48:01.546
there is no fighting
for such things.

673
00:48:03.881 --> 00:48:08.386
Just demons playing their games

674
00:48:08.469 --> 00:48:09.887
at other people's expense.

675
00:48:12.432 --> 00:48:16.769
If this is the future
I fought for. let me die.

676
00:48:34.912 --> 00:48:38.291
As a child. did you ever imagine

677
00:48:38.374 --> 00:48:42.629
you would be more cruel and
deadly than the worst of us?

678
00:48:47.300 --> 00:48:49.385
Or did you imagine
something better?

679
00:49:13.701 --> 00:49:15.078
After two successful tests.

680
00:49:15.161 --> 00:49:17.497
we will now be testing
remote capabilities.

681
00:49:17.580 --> 00:49:18.974
The first test. the
subjects were simply

682
00:49:18.998 --> 00:49:21.167
given audio commands.
and both sessions

683
00:49:21.250 --> 00:49:23.336
were an absolute success.

684
00:49:23.419 --> 00:49:25.380
We will now be incorporating
VR headsets

685
00:49:25.463 --> 00:49:29.425
for more specific. immediate.
and instant control.

686
00:49:36.099 --> 00:49:38.309
You control Queen Hangbe.
I will control Khan.

687
00:49:56.619 --> 00:49:59.622
Give audio commands
to Shaka Zulu.

688
00:49:59.706 --> 00:50:01.833
Shaka Zulu.
when you're attacked.

689
00:50:01.916 --> 00:50:05.336
defend yourself at all costs.

690
00:50:08.172 --> 00:50:09.465
[grunting]

691
00:50:15.930 --> 00:50:18.516
[shouting]

692
00:50:31.112 --> 00:50:32.822
[grunting]

693
00:50:32.905 --> 00:50:34.031
[cracks]

694
00:50:37.660 --> 00:50:38.995
<i>Connection lost.</i>

695
00:50:39.078 --> 00:50:40.955
<i>Resurrection sequence activated.</i>

696
00:50:41.038 --> 00:50:42.707
Well. that answers that.

697
00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:47.962
<i>If they die. we can no
longer control them.</i>

698
00:51:00.808 --> 00:51:02.268
[grunting]

699
00:51:13.154 --> 00:51:15.990
<i>Shaka Zulu. you may
stop fighting.</i>

700
00:51:16.073 --> 00:51:17.116
<i>You are the victor.</i>

701
00:51:25.792 --> 00:51:28.544
There.
They went in there.

702
00:51:29.962 --> 00:51:31.005
Come on.

703
00:51:31.088 --> 00:51:32.882
I can't.

704
00:51:32.965 --> 00:51:35.259
Yes. yes. you're tired.
Come on.

705
00:51:35.343 --> 00:51:37.053
I'm not just tired.

706
00:51:37.136 --> 00:51:39.555
It's poison.

707
00:51:39.639 --> 00:51:41.891
I can feel it killing me.

708
00:51:44.143 --> 00:51:46.663
I knew we weren't going to make
it there the whole way together.

709
00:51:49.857 --> 00:51:50.858
It was you.

710
00:51:52.985 --> 00:51:54.028
Not our captors.

711
00:51:55.613 --> 00:51:57.132
You poisoned me
when you were attending

712
00:51:57.156 --> 00:51:58.616
to the wound from the arrow.

713
00:52:00.910 --> 00:52:01.910
From the powder.

714
00:52:03.162 --> 00:52:04.288
I thought we were allies.

715
00:52:06.374 --> 00:52:07.750
When it was prudent.

716
00:52:10.294 --> 00:52:12.046
But now I must win
the Crimson Havoc.

717
00:52:13.548 --> 00:52:15.675
With it. I will
get that information

718
00:52:15.758 --> 00:52:16.801
to defeat the Romans.

719
00:52:19.053 --> 00:52:20.596
And nothing stands in my way.

720
00:52:25.142 --> 00:52:26.561
[shuddering]

721
00:52:45.830 --> 00:52:47.039
[sighs]

722
00:52:52.879 --> 00:52:54.422
Boudica falls.

723
00:52:54.505 --> 00:52:57.216
All hail the
Apothecary Queen. Cleopatra.

724
00:53:05.433 --> 00:53:08.102
Why bother with food.
fur. or feelings?

725
00:53:08.185 --> 00:53:11.606
Loyal. obedient. disposable.

726
00:53:11.689 --> 00:53:15.902
Just remember. when your
subscription ends. so do they.

727
00:53:15.985 --> 00:53:19.572
Pet pods. because love
should be manageable.

728
00:53:21.365 --> 00:53:22.742
Oh. that's our third kill.

729
00:53:22.825 --> 00:53:24.869
Boudica is down at
the hands of Cleopatra.

730
00:53:24.952 --> 00:53:27.204
who she thought was her ally.

731
00:53:27.288 --> 00:53:29.040
This is unprecedented.

732
00:53:29.123 --> 00:53:32.126
Cleopatra is following
the remaining four combatants.

733
00:53:32.209 --> 00:53:35.296
The match zone does not extend
into those maintenance tunnels.

734
00:53:35.379 --> 00:53:37.548
No live feed. no telemetry.

735
00:53:37.632 --> 00:53:40.426
They are outside
the parameters of the match

736
00:53:40.509 --> 00:53:42.345
and outside the rules entirely.

737
00:53:42.428 --> 00:53:44.531
I don't know what their plan is.
or even if they have one.

738
00:53:44.555 --> 00:53:46.599
but whatever it is.

739
00:53:46.682 --> 00:53:48.100
it's not part of
the game anymore.

740
00:53:51.729 --> 00:53:53.064
ATTILA:
It's massive in here.

741
00:53:53.147 --> 00:53:58.027
Endless halls.
all sealed like tombs.

742
00:53:58.110 --> 00:54:00.571
No voices. no footsteps.

743
00:54:00.655 --> 00:54:03.616
Joan. are you certain
they're in here?

744
00:54:03.699 --> 00:54:05.910
They have to be.

745
00:54:05.993 --> 00:54:07.703
No one guards an
empty space this fiercely.

746
00:54:08.829 --> 00:54:11.332
Shall I break one open?

747
00:54:11.415 --> 00:54:13.042
Perhaps our enemies
hide behind them.

748
00:54:13.125 --> 00:54:17.338
No. we must act with wisdom.
not with rage.

749
00:54:18.881 --> 00:54:20.161
There's a reason for every lock.

750
00:54:25.554 --> 00:54:27.181
Attila. stop!

751
00:54:27.264 --> 00:54:30.142
One move and your
blood stains the floor.

752
00:54:30.226 --> 00:54:32.061
Wait. I could have just
kept following you

753
00:54:32.144 --> 00:54:33.688
in the shadows
like I've been doing.

754
00:54:33.771 --> 00:54:35.940
Instead I've chosen
to show myself.

755
00:54:36.023 --> 00:54:37.400
Is that not proof I seek peace?

756
00:54:40.236 --> 00:54:41.236
Let her go.

757
00:54:43.322 --> 00:54:45.574
I offer truce.

758
00:54:45.658 --> 00:54:47.868
I regret the company
I have kept.

759
00:54:47.952 --> 00:54:50.871
They believe only in bloodshed.

760
00:54:50.955 --> 00:54:52.039
I do not.

761
00:54:53.582 --> 00:54:55.376
And what caused
the change of heart?

762
00:54:56.794 --> 00:54:59.338
I am not bred for battle.

763
00:54:59.422 --> 00:55:02.591
My place is among
the scrolls and courts.

764
00:55:02.675 --> 00:55:04.760
and not fields of war.

765
00:55:06.262 --> 00:55:07.722
I do not trust her.

766
00:55:07.805 --> 00:55:10.558
Nor I.

767
00:55:10.641 --> 00:55:13.853
I have pleaded for unity
since the beginning.

768
00:55:13.936 --> 00:55:16.564
I will not turn away
the first who seeks it.

769
00:55:20.401 --> 00:55:22.403
But betray us. Cleopatra.

770
00:55:22.486 --> 00:55:24.530
and you will answer to us all.

771
00:55:29.493 --> 00:55:31.454
This is a mistake.

772
00:55:31.537 --> 00:55:33.414
Then we will watch her closely.

773
00:55:35.499 --> 00:55:39.462
Cleopatra. if you deceive us.
I will be the one to kill you.

774
00:55:39.545 --> 00:55:41.464
You will not need to.

775
00:55:41.547 --> 00:55:44.216
I wish only to return
to my own time.

776
00:55:59.190 --> 00:56:00.190
Bring her out.

777
00:56:00.232 --> 00:56:02.234
<i>Anesthesia 40%.</i>

778
00:56:02.318 --> 00:56:04.028
I get it.

779
00:56:04.111 --> 00:56:06.405
The wars you fought
were of a different age.

780
00:56:06.489 --> 00:56:08.032
of a different time.

781
00:56:08.115 --> 00:56:10.993
When your husband.
King Prasutagus. died.

782
00:56:11.077 --> 00:56:13.788
Rome betrayed you.
but did you give up? No.

783
00:56:13.871 --> 00:56:16.791
You rose against them with a
hundred thousand men behind you.

784
00:56:16.874 --> 00:56:18.542
Spare me your speeches.

785
00:56:18.626 --> 00:56:21.879
Tyrants always have new ways
to hurt the weak.

786
00:56:21.962 --> 00:56:23.923
Your weapons may be strange.

787
00:56:24.006 --> 00:56:27.927
but your hearts are
as black as the Romans.

788
00:56:28.010 --> 00:56:30.471
The gods will judge you.

789
00:56:30.554 --> 00:56:32.056
The Just will always rise.

790
00:56:33.641 --> 00:56:34.809
[grunting]

791
00:56:39.271 --> 00:56:40.689
[shrieks]

792
00:56:42.274 --> 00:56:43.776
Think you can cage a wolf?

793
00:56:49.365 --> 00:56:50.783
Take her away.

794
00:56:55.329 --> 00:56:56.789
She's ready.

795
00:56:56.872 --> 00:56:58.165
I'm going to clean this up.

796
00:57:01.168 --> 00:57:02.168
Aria. all good?

797
00:57:03.295 --> 00:57:04.797
Great.

798
00:57:04.880 --> 00:57:06.799
We can't afford any
mistakes right now.

799
00:57:06.882 --> 00:57:09.593
That's why I went this route.

800
00:57:09.677 --> 00:57:11.262
How are the investors?

801
00:57:11.345 --> 00:57:13.013
The investors are fine.

802
00:57:13.097 --> 00:57:14.217
Everyone's online and ready.

803
00:57:15.182 --> 00:57:18.060
Good. Focus on that.

804
00:57:18.144 --> 00:57:20.729
Wait. Hold on.
I don't see them.

805
00:57:26.569 --> 00:57:27.486
ATTILA:
I hear something.

806
00:57:27.570 --> 00:57:28.737
[gasps]

807
00:57:28.821 --> 00:57:30.406
This way.

808
00:57:34.118 --> 00:57:36.912
What do you see?

809
00:57:50.759 --> 00:57:53.179
It's pure water.

810
00:57:53.262 --> 00:57:54.805
No well. no river.

811
00:58:00.519 --> 00:58:02.229
This belongs to Madame Wellman.

812
00:58:04.231 --> 00:58:05.774
What is this. a weapon?

813
00:58:13.032 --> 00:58:15.659
Perhaps to summon the guards.

814
00:58:15.743 --> 00:58:17.203
Or worse.

815
00:58:18.329 --> 00:58:20.831
MAMA:
Press it again.

816
00:58:20.915 --> 00:58:23.334
Don't.

817
00:58:23.417 --> 00:58:26.670
If you touch it. you will die.

818
00:58:26.754 --> 00:58:28.464
She lies.

819
00:58:28.547 --> 00:58:32.676
Just put it down.

820
00:58:32.760 --> 00:58:35.596
Perhaps if we push it. she dies.

821
00:58:35.679 --> 00:58:37.348
She's the problem.

822
00:58:37.431 --> 00:58:39.516
She's dead either way.

823
00:58:39.600 --> 00:58:42.019
You are defenseless now.

824
00:58:42.102 --> 00:58:43.854
No.

825
00:58:43.938 --> 00:58:46.190
- She is helping us.
- She is our captor.

826
00:58:46.273 --> 00:58:47.399
We should end this.

827
00:58:49.860 --> 00:58:51.612
That woman holds no power now.

828
00:58:53.781 --> 00:58:54.907
I saw you as specimens.

829
00:58:54.990 --> 00:58:56.784
Your lives were
never mine to use.

830
00:58:56.867 --> 00:58:57.952
I'm so sorry.

831
00:58:58.035 --> 00:58:58.953
So she says.

832
00:58:59.036 --> 00:59:02.039
But I vow to help you now.

833
00:59:02.122 --> 00:59:03.874
I can get you home.

834
00:59:03.958 --> 00:59:05.876
All of you. safely.

835
00:59:05.960 --> 00:59:09.755
Says the serpent handing
fruit to a child.

836
00:59:09.838 --> 00:59:12.675
You hold the button.

837
00:59:12.758 --> 00:59:15.052
But whose fate?

838
00:59:16.262 --> 00:59:17.596
Does it matter?

839
00:59:23.394 --> 00:59:25.980
What are those boxes
you keep looking at. Aria?

840
00:59:26.063 --> 00:59:27.898
Cameras.
They're watching us.

841
00:59:27.982 --> 00:59:30.693
The gaze from the gods?

842
00:59:30.776 --> 00:59:33.070
They think so. but
they're just humans like me.

843
00:59:33.153 --> 00:59:34.530
Are they watching us now?

844
00:59:34.613 --> 00:59:36.573
No. I have them on a video loop.

845
00:59:36.657 --> 00:59:38.033
But it won't last long.

846
00:59:38.117 --> 00:59:39.535
They're going to figure it out.

847
00:59:39.618 --> 00:59:41.537
Tell us. new friend.

848
00:59:41.620 --> 00:59:43.414
What is the truth here?

849
00:59:44.999 --> 00:59:46.208
What are you hiding?

850
00:59:47.543 --> 00:59:51.547
Whether you survive or not.

851
00:59:51.630 --> 00:59:54.466
you all will be sold
to the highest bidder.

852
00:59:54.550 --> 00:59:55.884
Like slaves?

853
00:59:55.968 --> 00:59:57.070
I should push this
button right now!

854
00:59:57.094 --> 00:59:58.429
- I am slave to no one!
- No!

855
00:59:58.512 --> 01:00:00.639
She tells us this
because she trusts us.

856
01:00:00.723 --> 01:00:02.641
She could have
withheld the information.

857
01:00:02.725 --> 01:00:05.144
Remember that.

858
01:00:05.227 --> 01:00:06.979
I press this button.

859
01:00:07.062 --> 01:00:08.605
Don't.

860
01:00:08.689 --> 01:00:13.569
I know. It's barbaric.
It is unforgivable.

861
01:00:13.652 --> 01:00:16.989
But if you press that button
now. you'll die.

862
01:00:21.243 --> 01:00:23.120
I know how to deactivate it.

863
01:00:46.727 --> 01:00:47.727
[sighs]

864
01:00:48.771 --> 01:00:50.481
We are safe?

865
01:00:50.564 --> 01:00:51.940
For now.

866
01:00:52.024 --> 01:00:54.568
Now let me take you all home.

867
01:01:05.579 --> 01:01:07.699
It'll take a little time
to power up the time machine.

868
01:01:11.085 --> 01:01:12.586
[machine beeps]

869
01:01:12.669 --> 01:01:15.839
Hold on. Hold on.
I got something. Machine room.

870
01:01:15.923 --> 01:01:18.008
Aria's powering up
the time machine.

871
01:01:18.092 --> 01:01:21.178
She's trying to send them back.

872
01:01:21.261 --> 01:01:22.554
She lied to us. Leon.

873
01:01:22.638 --> 01:01:25.808
What can we do?

874
01:01:25.891 --> 01:01:27.351
We can stall her.

875
01:01:27.434 --> 01:01:28.834
I'll shut the machine
down remotely.

876
01:01:32.189 --> 01:01:33.941
I have to restart the machine.

877
01:01:34.024 --> 01:01:35.609
Will that take time?

878
01:01:35.692 --> 01:01:37.403
It should just
take a few minutes.

879
01:01:37.486 --> 01:01:38.737
We'll patrol the threshold.

880
01:01:41.949 --> 01:01:43.283
Come on!

881
01:01:43.367 --> 01:01:45.244
[beeping]

882
01:01:45.327 --> 01:01:47.704
Remote reinitialization
in progress.

883
01:01:47.788 --> 01:01:49.832
That's your big play.
Shutting it down?

884
01:01:51.083 --> 01:01:52.626
Let's go find her. Leon.

885
01:01:52.709 --> 01:01:53.937
she's letting a billion
dollars get away.

886
01:01:53.961 --> 01:01:55.462
No. she's not.

887
01:01:55.546 --> 01:01:56.986
She's unwittingly
pushing the limits.

888
01:02:00.092 --> 01:02:01.802
Welcome back.

889
01:02:01.885 --> 01:02:03.929
Your new assignment:

890
01:02:04.012 --> 01:02:09.768
Kill all the remaining warriors
in the machine room.

891
01:02:09.852 --> 01:02:12.896
And Aria?

892
01:02:12.980 --> 01:02:14.540
I don't think
she's on our side anymore.

893
01:02:17.443 --> 01:02:18.986
49%.

894
01:02:19.069 --> 01:02:20.069
God grant us speed.

895
01:02:21.113 --> 01:02:22.406
It's the others.

896
01:02:22.489 --> 01:02:23.949
Stand ready.

897
01:02:24.032 --> 01:02:25.826
Stand your ground.

898
01:02:25.909 --> 01:02:26.994
Shadows approach.

899
01:02:28.787 --> 01:02:31.123
Damn it. 61 percent.

900
01:02:33.083 --> 01:02:36.587
<i>Mama Huaco and Attila the
Hun versus Ghengis Khan.</i>

901
01:02:36.670 --> 01:02:39.882
<i>Boudica. Shaka Zulu
and Queen Hangbe.</i>

902
01:02:39.965 --> 01:02:41.592
[grunting. shouting]

903
01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:48.807
81 percent!

904
01:02:48.891 --> 01:02:50.309
Give us speed. o Lord!

905
01:03:02.738 --> 01:03:03.738
[grunts]

906
01:03:07.743 --> 01:03:09.036
Attila!

907
01:03:12.414 --> 01:03:14.124
Let them return to their home.

908
01:03:15.918 --> 01:03:19.004
My spirit rides with you. Mama.

909
01:03:19.087 --> 01:03:21.965
It is a warrior's honor.

910
01:03:24.593 --> 01:03:27.221
May my ancestors
be prepared to receive me.

911
01:03:39.816 --> 01:03:41.026
[screaming]

912
01:03:44.905 --> 01:03:45.989
[gasps]

913
01:04:11.473 --> 01:04:12.975
[machine whirring]

914
01:04:14.977 --> 01:04:18.021
Almost there.
94%.

915
01:04:18.105 --> 01:04:19.982
Joan. on the bottom
of the machine.

916
01:04:20.065 --> 01:04:21.692
you'll see a series of switches.

917
01:04:21.775 --> 01:04:23.535
Make sure that they're
in the ready position.

918
01:04:23.610 --> 01:04:25.028
You'll know that they're ready

919
01:04:25.112 --> 01:04:26.738
because the lights
will turn green.

920
01:04:30.576 --> 01:04:31.785
The lights are green.

921
01:04:31.868 --> 01:04:32.869
The path is prepared.

922
01:04:32.953 --> 01:04:33.996
Yes!

923
01:04:34.079 --> 01:04:35.080
Yes...

924
01:04:35.163 --> 01:04:36.915
What now?

925
01:04:36.999 --> 01:04:37.999
Cleo...

926
01:04:39.418 --> 01:04:40.418
[exhales]

927
01:04:43.255 --> 01:04:45.132
I knew it.

928
01:04:45.215 --> 01:04:46.258
Cleo

929
01:04:51.638 --> 01:04:52.889
99%.

930
01:04:52.973 --> 01:04:54.641
Are the switches ready?

931
01:04:54.725 --> 01:04:56.393
All is as it should be.

932
01:04:56.476 --> 01:04:58.353
Where's Joan?

933
01:04:58.437 --> 01:05:01.106
She remains behind to make
certain the glow stays green.

934
01:05:07.529 --> 01:05:09.489
Joan!
Do not trust her.

935
01:05:12.826 --> 01:05:13.826
Where is Joan?

936
01:05:18.248 --> 01:05:19.248
Joan!

937
01:05:41.229 --> 01:05:42.814
[grunting]

938
01:05:42.898 --> 01:05:45.233
Oda Nobunaga vs.
Queen Hangbe.

939
01:05:45.317 --> 01:05:47.736
Shaka Zulu. and Boudica.

940
01:05:54.159 --> 01:05:55.159
[grunting]

941
01:06:10.967 --> 01:06:12.302
[grunts]

942
01:06:13.679 --> 01:06:15.722
Wait. Stay your hands.

943
01:06:18.433 --> 01:06:20.435
I alone remain.

944
01:06:20.519 --> 01:06:21.978
I am the last.

945
01:06:23.271 --> 01:06:25.357
I am victorious.

946
01:06:25.440 --> 01:06:27.109
I win!

947
01:06:28.985 --> 01:06:30.821
<i>Let her live.</i>

948
01:06:30.904 --> 01:06:32.155
Put down your weapons.

949
01:06:40.580 --> 01:06:43.500
Take Cleopatra to
the treatment room.

950
01:06:43.583 --> 01:06:45.419
Lock Aria up in
the holding cells.

951
01:07:06.231 --> 01:07:07.231
[grunts]

952
01:07:11.778 --> 01:07:12.779
Is anyone there?

953
01:07:12.863 --> 01:07:14.322
I hear distress.

954
01:07:14.406 --> 01:07:16.283
It's just me.

955
01:07:16.366 --> 01:07:17.367
Madame Wellman?

956
01:07:24.499 --> 01:07:25.876
[grunting]

957
01:07:33.300 --> 01:07:34.468
Don't.

958
01:07:36.553 --> 01:07:38.680
Meet me back at
the machine room.

959
01:07:38.764 --> 01:07:39.848
It's two floors down.

960
01:07:39.931 --> 01:07:41.850
The stair is over there.

961
01:07:41.933 --> 01:07:43.613
Take a right at the
bottom of the stairway.

962
01:07:43.643 --> 01:07:44.686
I will meet you there.

963
01:07:44.770 --> 01:07:46.271
Okay.
And the others?

964
01:07:46.354 --> 01:07:47.814
I'm getting them.

965
01:08:33.026 --> 01:08:35.320
Leon. it's Joan.

966
01:08:35.403 --> 01:08:37.155
She escaped from her cell.

967
01:08:41.201 --> 01:08:42.201
Bring Joan now.

968
01:09:08.520 --> 01:09:10.105
- Joan. I told you!
- Silence!

969
01:09:10.188 --> 01:09:12.315
Make haste to the machine
room. I shall delay them.

970
01:09:16.903 --> 01:09:17.903
Flee! Now!

971
01:09:21.700 --> 01:09:26.371
<i>Joan of Arc. this is your
final warning to surrender.</i>

972
01:09:26.454 --> 01:09:28.790
Lord. guide my hand.

973
01:09:28.874 --> 01:09:29.916
Lend me. as you will.

974
01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:31.167
Shield me from evil and

975
01:09:34.212 --> 01:09:36.798
walk the path of righteousness!

976
01:09:41.511 --> 01:09:43.597
The TCA has confirmed that
a minor incident occurred

977
01:09:43.680 --> 01:09:45.515
today inside the
Crimson Havoc facility

978
01:09:45.599 --> 01:09:47.517
when several contestants
inadvertently entered

979
01:09:47.601 --> 01:09:49.394
a restricted maintenance zone.

980
01:09:49.477 --> 01:09:52.063
Officials say the breach was
the result of a navigation error

981
01:09:52.147 --> 01:09:53.732
during a routine match segment

982
01:09:53.815 --> 01:09:55.626
and that the situation
was resolved without risk

983
01:09:55.650 --> 01:09:57.235
to the public or the games.

984
01:09:57.319 --> 01:09:59.696
While social media has
been circulating unauthorized

985
01:09:59.779 --> 01:10:01.114
footage of the incident.

986
01:10:01.197 --> 01:10:02.741
viewers are reminded
that such material

987
01:10:02.824 --> 01:10:05.243
is often misleading
and taken out of context.

988
01:10:05.327 --> 01:10:07.245
The TCA encourages fans to focus

989
01:10:07.329 --> 01:10:08.830
on the thrilling
competition ahead

990
01:10:08.914 --> 01:10:10.749
rather than rumors
and has emphasized

991
01:10:10.832 --> 01:10:13.251
that Crimson Havoc remains
safe. secure.

992
01:10:13.335 --> 01:10:16.171
and on schedule with
no impact to upcoming events.

993
01:10:20.467 --> 01:10:22.344
[grunting]

994
01:10:28.099 --> 01:10:29.476
[grunts]

995
01:10:45.450 --> 01:10:48.244
Oh...
It is destroyed!

996
01:10:48.328 --> 01:10:49.371
I am afraid so.

997
01:10:50.914 --> 01:10:52.791
The only way back
to your time is broken.

998
01:10:54.084 --> 01:10:56.044
They have taken what is vital.

999
01:10:56.127 --> 01:10:59.047
We are all stuck here forever.

1000
01:11:13.728 --> 01:11:14.938
Unless we change our fate.

1001
01:11:16.481 --> 01:11:18.024
Cleopatra!

1002
01:11:18.108 --> 01:11:20.068
But how is this possible?

1003
01:11:20.151 --> 01:11:21.903
I devised an antidote
to shield my mind

1004
01:11:21.987 --> 01:11:24.280
from their poison. this powder.

1005
01:11:27.283 --> 01:11:30.161
Joan. I owe you an apology.

1006
01:11:30.245 --> 01:11:31.621
You owe me nothing.

1007
01:11:31.705 --> 01:11:35.625
No. I must speak the truth.

1008
01:11:35.709 --> 01:11:38.044
I meant to kill you.

1009
01:11:38.128 --> 01:11:41.172
not as a slave to their will.
but of my choosing.

1010
01:11:42.757 --> 01:11:45.343
You got in my way.

1011
01:11:45.427 --> 01:11:48.388
but your words.

1012
01:11:48.471 --> 01:11:50.932
your faith.

1013
01:11:51.016 --> 01:11:54.853
your selflessness.
they affected me.

1014
01:11:56.730 --> 01:11:59.941
We seek the same thing.
you and I:

1015
01:12:00.025 --> 01:12:03.194
A way home and freedom
for our people.

1016
01:12:04.529 --> 01:12:05.613
I see that now.

1017
01:12:07.365 --> 01:12:09.200
Then we are allies at last.

1018
01:12:10.577 --> 01:12:14.622
I trusted you would find a way.

1019
01:12:14.706 --> 01:12:17.375
but is there a way
to fix the machine?

1020
01:12:19.085 --> 01:12:20.587
Our hope is Aria.

1021
01:12:20.670 --> 01:12:22.172
She made this device.

1022
01:12:23.923 --> 01:12:24.924
Then we find her.

1023
01:12:28.386 --> 01:12:29.637
And the others?

1024
01:12:32.974 --> 01:12:35.268
This is the antidote.

1025
01:12:35.351 --> 01:12:38.146
If you encounter them.
make them breathe it in.

1026
01:12:38.229 --> 01:12:39.773
And when their minds are freed.

1027
01:12:39.856 --> 01:12:41.483
you must persuade
them to join us.

1028
01:12:50.408 --> 01:12:52.327
[grunting]

1029
01:12:52.410 --> 01:12:54.662
Joan of Arc vs.
Oda Nobunaga

1030
01:12:56.414 --> 01:12:57.957
[shrieks]

1031
01:13:04.756 --> 01:13:05.965
[grunting]

1032
01:13:10.011 --> 01:13:11.179
[groans]

1033
01:13:26.069 --> 01:13:29.781
What?
What is this?

1034
01:13:29.864 --> 01:13:31.300
They've enslaved all
but Cleopatra and I

1035
01:13:31.324 --> 01:13:32.826
under mind control.

1036
01:13:32.909 --> 01:13:36.037
She developed an antidote.
but we need your help.

1037
01:13:37.997 --> 01:13:39.207
You trust her now?

1038
01:13:39.290 --> 01:13:40.667
I do.

1039
01:13:40.750 --> 01:13:44.170
She spared my life
and revealed her truth.

1040
01:13:44.254 --> 01:13:45.254
I believe in her.

1041
01:13:46.798 --> 01:13:48.800
Then I stand with you.

1042
01:13:48.883 --> 01:13:53.096
I failed you once by not
warning you of the poison.

1043
01:13:53.179 --> 01:13:54.472
I will not fail you again.

1044
01:13:57.642 --> 01:14:00.520
You're a man of honor. Oda.

1045
01:14:00.603 --> 01:14:01.729
We will find them.

1046
01:14:04.232 --> 01:14:07.277
I don't like this.
This is taking too long.

1047
01:14:07.360 --> 01:14:08.840
We should go back
to the control room.

1048
01:14:11.656 --> 01:14:13.491
Status report.
Respond.

1049
01:14:15.994 --> 01:14:18.204
What's wrong?

1050
01:14:18.288 --> 01:14:20.206
Some sort of a transmission.

1051
01:14:22.584 --> 01:14:24.460
They're asking where you are.

1052
01:14:25.962 --> 01:14:27.002
Tell them you've slain me.

1053
01:14:30.216 --> 01:14:31.843
Joan is dead.

1054
01:14:31.926 --> 01:14:35.096
Very good.
Bring her body to us.

1055
01:14:35.180 --> 01:14:36.222
[machine chimes]

1056
01:14:36.306 --> 01:14:37.473
You heard that. right?

1057
01:14:41.352 --> 01:14:44.189
That was definitely Joan.

1058
01:14:44.272 --> 01:14:46.524
She must have freed him
from mind control somehow.

1059
01:14:57.118 --> 01:14:58.118
[grunting]

1060
01:15:00.914 --> 01:15:03.082
<i>Joan of Arc and Oda Nobunaga</i>

1061
01:15:03.166 --> 01:15:04.918
<i>versus Boudica and
Attila the Hun.</i>

1062
01:15:20.099 --> 01:15:21.309
[shouting]

1063
01:15:30.485 --> 01:15:32.445
[grunting]

1064
01:15:36.824 --> 01:15:38.159
[coughs]

1065
01:15:45.792 --> 01:15:46.792
We...

1066
01:15:48.795 --> 01:15:50.129
Leave.

1067
01:15:53.508 --> 01:15:54.592
Welcome back. my friend.

1068
01:16:06.854 --> 01:16:08.439
Now we know how Joan escaped.

1069
01:16:08.523 --> 01:16:10.441
Aria. she's gone.

1070
01:16:10.525 --> 01:16:13.403
She played us the whole time.

1071
01:16:13.486 --> 01:16:15.280
I'll have to cycle
through the cam...

1072
01:16:15.363 --> 01:16:16.572
[grunting]

1073
01:16:26.499 --> 01:16:27.709
Aria!

1074
01:16:30.378 --> 01:16:31.754
What the hell?

1075
01:16:31.838 --> 01:16:33.798
We were supposed to
be in this together!

1076
01:16:33.881 --> 01:16:37.260
It was never about
either of you!

1077
01:16:37.343 --> 01:16:38.386
What is it about?

1078
01:16:41.889 --> 01:16:44.100
Leon. get off of her!

1079
01:16:44.183 --> 01:16:46.144
Leon. stop!
That's enough!

1080
01:17:00.325 --> 01:17:02.535
Aria...

1081
01:17:02.618 --> 01:17:04.871
This was supposed to
change all of our lives.

1082
01:17:04.954 --> 01:17:07.999
I used to believe that.

1083
01:17:08.082 --> 01:17:10.376
But now I see they're
not toys for billionaires.

1084
01:17:10.460 --> 01:17:12.211
They're human beings.

1085
01:17:12.295 --> 01:17:15.548
and we tore them from their own
lives for our selfish spectacle.

1086
01:17:15.631 --> 01:17:17.467
How sanctimonious of you.

1087
01:17:17.550 --> 01:17:20.845
What if...

1088
01:17:20.928 --> 01:17:23.014
What if we put
the time machine back?

1089
01:17:23.097 --> 01:17:26.267
You fix it.
and we send everybody home.

1090
01:17:27.643 --> 01:17:29.312
Okay. let's do it.

1091
01:17:29.395 --> 01:17:30.980
And you try anything.
and I'll stop.

1092
01:17:31.064 --> 01:17:34.067
Is that right?

1093
01:17:34.150 --> 01:17:37.945
You don't trust me.
And I don't trust you.

1094
01:17:38.029 --> 01:17:40.198
So we'll both go
to the machine room.

1095
01:17:40.281 --> 01:17:42.325
But I want this. Gordon.

1096
01:17:42.408 --> 01:17:45.453
I want an escort with drones.

1097
01:17:46.579 --> 01:17:48.623
Is that really necessary?

1098
01:17:48.706 --> 01:17:50.500
The drones are not
even built for indoors.

1099
01:17:50.583 --> 01:17:53.169
I'm not walking into an ambush.

1100
01:17:53.252 --> 01:17:57.340
I'm fine with that.

1101
01:17:57.423 --> 01:17:58.883
Fine.

1102
01:17:58.966 --> 01:17:59.966
Go.

1103
01:18:11.896 --> 01:18:13.147
You made it.

1104
01:18:13.231 --> 01:18:14.231
I did.

1105
01:18:14.273 --> 01:18:15.483
Everyone is safe.

1106
01:18:15.566 --> 01:18:17.110
I will go find Aria.

1107
01:18:17.193 --> 01:18:19.195
Wait. Take this.

1108
01:18:19.278 --> 01:18:21.239
It's a fast-acting poison.

1109
01:18:21.322 --> 01:18:23.002
It quickly spreads
through your bloodstream

1110
01:18:23.032 --> 01:18:25.493
the moment it's ingested.

1111
01:18:25.576 --> 01:18:26.702
Use it for our captors.

1112
01:18:26.786 --> 01:18:29.122
Okay.

1113
01:18:29.205 --> 01:18:30.790
Or for yourself.
if you are captured.

1114
01:18:30.873 --> 01:18:32.041
and prefer a quick death.

1115
01:18:40.383 --> 01:18:41.384
Protect this machine.

1116
01:18:43.428 --> 01:18:44.470
And each other.

1117
01:18:47.140 --> 01:18:48.933
Our honor is all we have left.

1118
01:18:52.770 --> 01:18:54.897
They're not your friends.
You understand that. right?

1119
01:18:54.981 --> 01:18:56.858
They're killers.
They think nothing of you.

1120
01:18:56.941 --> 01:18:59.068
And you know nothing about them.

1121
01:19:02.864 --> 01:19:07.827
<i>Identify Joan of Arc.</i>

1122
01:19:07.910 --> 01:19:10.204
The drones are still
programmed to kill Joan.

1123
01:19:10.288 --> 01:19:11.539
Run!

1124
01:19:11.622 --> 01:19:12.915
<i>Eliminate Joan of Arc.</i>

1125
01:19:14.667 --> 01:19:19.005
<i>Eliminate Joan of Arc.
Eliminate Joan of Arc.</i>

1126
01:19:19.088 --> 01:19:20.548
<i>Eliminate Joan of Arc.</i>

1127
01:19:20.631 --> 01:19:22.091
<i>Abort.</i>

1128
01:19:22.175 --> 01:19:23.426
[grunting]

1129
01:19:42.945 --> 01:19:45.990
This is what happens
to traitors!

1130
01:19:46.073 --> 01:19:47.116
Guide my hand. oh Lord!

1131
01:20:00.588 --> 01:20:01.839
[beeping]

1132
01:20:04.675 --> 01:20:09.931
Joan! You won't regenerate
with the machine offline.

1133
01:20:10.014 --> 01:20:12.600
I will make peace
with the Almighty.

1134
01:20:16.270 --> 01:20:18.272
And you are free to
save my friends.

1135
01:20:20.024 --> 01:20:22.527
Go fix the machine.

1136
01:20:22.610 --> 01:20:23.819
Thank you so much.

1137
01:20:26.280 --> 01:20:29.992
And for what it's worth.
I'm sorry.

1138
01:20:49.595 --> 01:20:52.098
<i>GORDON: Joan. go left at
the end of the corridor.</i>

1139
01:20:52.181 --> 01:20:53.367
<i>You can hide out
in the control room</i>

1140
01:20:53.391 --> 01:20:54.976
<i>until Aria fixes the machine.</i>

1141
01:20:55.059 --> 01:20:56.936
<i>Control room doors opening.</i>

1142
01:21:01.023 --> 01:21:02.358
<i>Control room doors closing.</i>

1143
01:21:05.194 --> 01:21:06.320
<i>Control room doors opening.</i>

1144
01:21:06.404 --> 01:21:07.613
The drone!

1145
01:21:10.157 --> 01:21:11.158
[screams]

1146
01:21:22.003 --> 01:21:23.087
[gasps]

1147
01:21:33.264 --> 01:21:35.474
How is it you live?

1148
01:21:35.558 --> 01:21:36.892
I...

1149
01:21:38.227 --> 01:21:40.313
I believed you lost to death.

1150
01:21:43.941 --> 01:21:45.192
I thought the same.

1151
01:21:47.445 --> 01:21:50.448
My last memory is of
that thunderous explosion

1152
01:21:50.531 --> 01:21:53.868
that descended upon us.

1153
01:21:53.951 --> 01:21:55.119
And the poison.

1154
01:21:55.202 --> 01:21:56.871
You took the poison?

1155
01:21:59.373 --> 01:22:02.460
I can explain.

1156
01:22:02.543 --> 01:22:08.299
I used Cleopatra's uploaded
knowledge to craft an antidote.

1157
01:22:08.382 --> 01:22:09.842
I thought that it was too late.

1158
01:22:09.925 --> 01:22:11.510
Both of you pulled through.

1159
01:22:11.594 --> 01:22:15.556
Honestly. those explosions
almost killed you.

1160
01:22:15.640 --> 01:22:16.640
The machine.

1161
01:22:18.142 --> 01:22:21.312
Will you still be able to...

1162
01:22:21.395 --> 01:22:24.148
Send you back
to your rightful time?

1163
01:22:24.231 --> 01:22:25.232
Yes.

1164
01:22:27.109 --> 01:22:28.109
Are you ready?

1165
01:22:29.487 --> 01:22:30.613
So soon?

1166
01:22:31.864 --> 01:22:32.907
Of course.

1167
01:22:35.910 --> 01:22:36.952
Come on.

1168
01:23:02.478 --> 01:23:04.814
Okay.
Remember your order.

1169
01:23:04.897 --> 01:23:07.108
Khan. you're up first.

1170
01:23:26.585 --> 01:23:28.713
Will these memories
remain with us?

1171
01:23:30.464 --> 01:23:31.632
Do you want them to?

1172
01:23:32.842 --> 01:23:33.843
No.

1173
01:23:34.844 --> 01:23:36.095
You'll not remember.

1174
01:23:41.600 --> 01:23:43.728
Our spirits will remember.

1175
01:23:50.192 --> 01:23:52.236
May fortune favor you. Aria.

1176
01:23:52.319 --> 01:23:55.239
I won the day.
but forfeited myself.

1177
01:23:55.322 --> 01:23:56.782
Me. too.

1178
01:24:00.327 --> 01:24:02.121
Such is the fate of mankind.

1179
01:24:09.462 --> 01:24:10.796
And all kind.

1180
01:25:08.604 --> 01:25:10.022
[engine starts]

1181
01:25:35.506 --> 01:25:36.590
[traffic noise]

1182
01:25:40.594 --> 01:25:41.929
[sighs]

1183
01:25:42.305 --> 01:26:42.943
Do you want subtitles for any video?
